      • createFileFromByteArray

        public static void createFileFromByteArray(byte[] fileBytes,
                                           java.lang.String path,
                                           java.lang.String name,
                                           java.lang.String extension,
                                           boolean isImageFile)
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Method to construct a file from an array of bytes. If file is an image, the file's extension parameter is ignored and the file is generated in jpg format.
        Parameters:
        fileBytes - Byte array that represents the file
        path - Path where the file will be saved
        name - Name will be given to the file (not including the format). If you want to create an image called "test.jpg", this parameter should only contain the string "test"
        extension - The file's extension (not for image files) without a dot (.)
        isImageFile - A boolean to indicate if you're creating an image or not
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
        Since:
        JSockets 1.0.0
